{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place lemongrass, onion, garlic, macadamia nuts, chilli, curry powder, ginger, turmeric, cumin, coriander (leaves, roots and stems), shrimp paste and 50 g of the coconut milk into mixing bowl and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat blending <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> , until a fine consistency is achieved. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter or ghee and cook <nobr>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add remaining 400 g of the coconut milk, water, stock paste, Kaffir lime leaves, fish sauce, lime juice and salt and cook <nobr>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh noodles into it. Cover noodles with boiling water and set aside to cook.","Add chicken to mixing bowl and cook <nobr>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add prawns and bok choy and cook <nobr>4-5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until prawns are cooked through. Carefully remove Kaffir lime leaves using a slotted spoon.","Drain rice noodles through simmering basket and divide noodles evenly between 4 serving bowls. Pour laksa over the top.","Garnish with bean sprouts, extra sliced chilli and extra coriander leaves before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 stalk fresh lemongrass, white part only, cut into pieces","1 brown onion, (approx. 150 g), cut into halves","4 garlic cloves","8 raw macadamia nuts","1 - 2 fresh bird's eye chillies, to taste, plus extra sliced for garnishing","1 tsp curry powder","5 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","1 tsp ground turmeric","1 tsp ground cumin seeds","2 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves, roots and stems, plus extra leaves for garnishing (see Tips)","1 tsp shrimp paste","450 g canned coconut milk","20 g butter","150 g water","2 tsp Chicken stock paste (see Tips)","8 fresh Kaffir lime leaves, bruised","1 tsp fish sauce","2 tsp lime juice","¼ tsp sea salt, to taste","200 g dried rice noodles (approx. 3 mm wide)","200 g skinless chicken thigh fillets, cut into cubes (2 cm)","300 g raw peeled prawns","180 g bok choy, cut into pieces","100 g bean sprouts, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r78368","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-G99a2JBdOvY\/XZMy8oTCWbI\/AAAAAAAAarc\/UZH9_7U4dCoQbG9pb22G0OpPYLWtlUPKwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RUvrfovZBpP5FphG.png","title":"Prawn and chicken laksa","publishedAt":"2014-09-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30 g","fat":"36 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"16 g","calories":"2156 kJ \/ 513 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, slotted spoon, serving bowls","hintsAndTricks":["To prepare coriander roots for use in the curry paste, remove all the fibrous small brown off-shoots from the main root by scraping with a teaspoon.","Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or the<em> Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","Shrimp paste, also known as belachan, can be found in the International aisle of most supermarkets or specialty Asian grocers."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","40m","4 portions"]}